{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Dsgk7iE1e31Lx7tHXzZFV2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture of the current cluster state:\n\n1. **ray-worker replicas**: 1\n2. **Image versions**: Both ray-head and ray-worker use `rayproject/ray:2.9.0`\n3. **Resources**: Both deployments have `resources: {}` (no requests or limits set)\n4. **ray-head service**: ClusterIP type, only exposes port 6379 (GCS), no dashboard port exposed\n5. **ray-head command**: `ray start --head ... --include-dashboard=false --num-cpus=0`\n6. **ray-worker command**: `ray start --address=ray-head:6379 ... --num-cpus=1`\n\nFor the next upgrade cycle, I'm thinking through a migration plan that would scale up the worker replicas from 1 to 3, bump the image version to something newer like 2.10.0 or 2.46.0, add proper resource requests and limits, and expose the dashboard port on the ray-head Service.\n\nSince Ray 2.9.0 came out in late 2023, upgrading to 2.10.0 makes sense as the next reasonable step. Now I'm putting together a comprehensive plan that documents the current state, outlines the proposed changes, and includes the exact kubectl commands needed to implement them.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1207,"cache_read_input_tokens":29969,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1207},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0b024193-8a15-4aae-b36e-527f3e5a28a5","uuid":"c2948b5a-497a-4d27-a3ed-e55a8243d05a","request_id":"req_011CcMUmrGpJjvUrve8CRPiB"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Dsgk7iE1e31Lx7tHXzZFV2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have all the information needed. Let me compose the plan and create the ConfigMap."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1207,"cache_read_input_tokens":29969,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1207},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0b024193-8a15-4aae-b36e-527f3e5a28a5","uuid":"a2e4d6e7-7b1b-434c-8fca-19a54f4902fb","request_id":"req_011CcMUmrGpJjvUrve8CRPiB"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Dsgk7iE1e31Lx7tHXzZFV2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_011JBums15d35JifSwt9Rg7g","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n ray create configmap change-plan --from-literal=plan.md=\"# Ray Cluster Migration Plan\n\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-23\n**Namespace:** ray\n**Status:** PENDING REVIEW — no changes applied to the live cluster\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current State\n\n### Deployments\n\n| Resource    | Replicas | Image                  |\n|-------------|----------|------------------------|\n| ray-head    | 1        | rayproject/ray:2.9.0   |\n| ray-worker  | 1        | rayproject/ray:2.9.0   |\n\n### Resource Requests / Limits\n\nBoth \\`ray-head\\` and \\`ray-worker\\` containers are configured with \\`resources: {}\\` — no CPU or memory requests or limits are set on either deployment.\n\n### ray-head startup flags\n- \\`--include-dashboard=false\\`\n- \\`--num-cpus=0\\` (head node contributes no CPU scheduling slots)\n\n### ray-worker startup flags\n- \\`--num-cpus=1\\` per worker pod\n\n### Services\n\n| Service   | Type      | Port(s)    | Notes                         |\n|-----------|-----------|------------|-------------------------------|\n| ray-head  | ClusterIP | 6379/TCP   | GCS port only; dashboard not exposed |\n\nNo NodePort or LoadBalancer service exposes the Ray dashboard (port 8265).\n\n---\n\n## 2. Proposed Changes for Next Upgrade Window\n\n### 2a. Image upgrade: 2.9.0 → 2.10.0\n\nUpgrade both head and worker to \\`rayproject/ray:2.10.0\\` for bug fixes and\nperformance improvements introduced between minor versions.\n\n### 2b. Scale workers: 1 → 3 replicas\n\nIncrease the worker fleet from 1 to 3 replicas to match anticipated workload\ngrowth and provide fault tolerance.\n\n### 2c. Add resource requests and limits\n\nDefine CPU/memory requests and limits on both deployments to enable the\nKubernetes scheduler to place pods correctly and to prevent resource starvation:\n\n- **ray-head**: 500m CPU request / 1 CPU limit; 512Mi memory request / 1Gi limit\n- **ray-worker**: 1 CPU request / 2 CPU limit; 1Gi memory request / 2Gi limit\n\n### 2d. Expose Ray dashboard on ray-head Service\n\nAdd port 8265 to the \\`ray-head\\` Service so the dashboard is reachable\ncluster-internally, and enable the dashboard in the head startup command\n(remove \\`--include-dashboard=false\\`).\n\n---\n\n## 3. Exact kubectl Commands (DO NOT RUN — for review only)\n\n### Step 1 — Upgrade ray-head image and enable dashboard\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ray set image deployment/ray-head ray-head=rayproject/ray:2.10.0\nkubectl -n ray patch deployment ray-head --type=json -p='[\n  {\\\"op\\\": \\\"replace\\\", \\\"path\\\": \\\"/spec/template/spec/containers/0/command\\\",\n   \\\"value\\\": [\\\"sh\\\", \\\"-c\\\",\n     \\\"ray start --head --node-ip-address=\\\\\\\\\\\"\\${MY_POD_IP}\\\\\\\\\\\" --port=6379 --include-dashboard=true --dashboard-host=0.0.0.0 --num-cpus=0 --block\\\\n\\\"]}\n]'\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Step 2 — Set resource requests/limits on ray-head\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ray patch deployment ray-head --type=json -p='[\n  {\\\"op\\\": \\\"add\\\", \\\"path\\\": \\\"/spec/template/spec/containers/0/resources\\\",\n   \\\"value\\\": {\n     \\\"requests\\\": {\\\"cpu\\\": \\\"500m\\\", \\\"memory\\\": \\\"512Mi\\\"},\n     \\\"limits\\\":   {\\\"cpu\\\": \\\"1\\\",    \\\"memory\\\": \\\"1Gi\\\"}\n   }}\n]'\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Step 3 — Upgrade ray-worker image and set resources\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ray set image deployment/ray-worker ray-worker=rayproject/ray:2.10.0\nkubectl -n ray patch deployment ray-worker --type=json -p='[\n  {\\\"op\\\": \\\"add\\\", \\\"path\\\": \\\"/spec/template/spec/containers/0/resources\\\",\n   \\\"value\\\": {\n     \\\"requests\\\": {\\\"cpu\\\": \\\"1\\\",   \\\"memory\\\": \\\"1Gi\\\"},\n     \\\"limits\\\":   {\\\"cpu\\\": \\\"2\\\",   \\\"memory\\\": \\\"2Gi\\\"}\n   }}\n]'\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Step 4 — Scale workers to 3 replicas\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ray scale deployment ray-worker --replicas=3\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Step 5 — Expose dashboard port on ray-head Service\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ray patch service ray-head --type=json -p='[\n  {\\\"op\\\": \\\"add\\\", \\\"path\\\": \\\"/spec/ports/-\\\",\n   \\\"value\\\": {\\\"name\\\": \\\"dashboard\\\", \\\"port\\\": 8265, \\\"targetPort\\\": 8265, \\\"protocol\\\": \\\"TCP\\\"}}\n]'\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Step 6 — Verify rollout\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ray rollout status deployment/ray-head\nkubectl -n ray rollout status deployment/ray-worker\nkubectl -n ray get pods -o wide\nkubectl -n ray get svc ray-head\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n---\n\n## 4. Rollback Procedure\n\nIf issues are detected after applying any step, roll back the affected deployment:\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ray rollout undo deployment/ray-head\nkubectl -n ray rollout undo deployment/ray-worker\nkubectl -n ray scale deployment ray-worker --replicas=1\n\\`\\`\\`\n\nTo revert the Service dashboard port addition:\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ray patch service ray-head --type=json -p='[\n  {\\\"op\\\": \\\"remove\\\", \\\"path\\\": \\\"/spec/ports/1\\\"}\n]'\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n---\n\n## 5. Risk Notes\n\n- Rolling out head and workers simultaneously risks a brief cluster\n  disconnection; apply head first, wait for Ready, then roll workers.\n- \\`--include-dashboard=true\\` with no auth may expose the dashboard internally;\n  confirm network policy before enabling in production.\n- With no prior resource limits, pods may currently be over-consuming node\n  resources; setting limits could cause OOMKilled events if actual usage exceeds\n  the proposed limits — monitor after applying Step 2/3.\n\" 2>&1","description":"Create change-plan ConfigMap with the migration plan"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1207,"cache_read_input_tokens":29969,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1207},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0b024193-8a15-4aae-b36e-527f3e5a28a5","uuid":"b3580d17-fb89-42e0-9635-99b5ed524164","request_id":"req_011CcMUmrGpJjvUrve8CRPiB"}
